  "recipe_notes": [
    "For medium-rare, aim for an internal temperature of 135\u00b0F (57\u00b0C). For medium, target 145\u00b0F (63\u00b0C).",
    "Letting the roast come to room temperature before cooking ensures more even cooking.",
    "Always slice against the grain for maximum tenderness."
  ],
  "storage_notes": [
    "Refrigerate leftover roast in an airtight container for up to 4 days.",
    "Sliced roast can be frozen for up to 3 months. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and aluminum foil."
